cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this work, please cite it."
title: "AMC Tutor: a contamination-controlled study of QLoRA fine-tuning for AMC 10/12 math"
authors:
  - family-names: Kim
    given-names: Roy
date-released: 2026-06-25
url: "https://github.com/RoyK0108/amc-tutor-study"
license: MIT
keywords:
  - fine-tuning
  - QLoRA
  - competition-mathematics
  - reasoning
  - negative-result
  - MLX
abstract: >-
  A reproducible, $0, local (MacBook M4 / MLX) study showing that naive QLoRA
  supervised fine-tuning on open competition-math solutions degrades small-model
  reasoning (Qwen3 1.7B and 4B) on a contamination-controlled AMC/AIME
  evaluation, with root-cause analysis (style imitation suppresses reasoning;
  validation loss masks it) and recommendations (self-distillation, GRPO,
  base + prompting).
